                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>Charleston, S. C.</placeName>\n                <date>Sept. 10. 5617/1857</date>.</p>\n            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir—More than four weeks ago<lb/> I addressed a letter to you,\n                with the request to send me<lb/> a copy of your octavo Bible bound in purple velvet,\n                with<lb/> gilded clasp &amp;c, designed for a nuptial present, and in-<lb/>close my\n                bill the amount of which I do not know. The<lb/> wedding took place yesterday, and I\n                have not yet received<lb/> the Bible, although I wrote that I wanted it in the\n                first<lb/> week of <date>September</date>. As it is, I would be glad, to\n                receive<lb/> it at least before <add>ר\"ה</add>. It is to be presented to\n                    <persName>Mrs.<lb/> Sarah I. Davega</persName>, formerly <persName>Mrs. I. J.\n                    Moses</persName>, sister to my wife.<lb/> What say to this news? No doubt, you\n                heard of this “match”<lb/> before, considering that you are generally <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">an courant</hi> with<lb/> all that transpires at least amongst\n                the Israelites of <placeName>Charles-<lb/>ton</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">But, have you been informed also of the<lb/> discussion which has\n                been carried on, for the last weeks, on<lb/> the subject of the Swiss Treaty, in the\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">Courier</hi> of this city? Have<lb/> you been informed\n                that, after I had published an Article, on<lb/> the <date>13<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi>\n                    of August</date> last, calling upon the Jews of\n                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, “to<lb/> act now in concert, and forget all\n                differences of religious opinion,” and appealing to the Press for assistance, “<hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">A Jew</hi>” appeared<lb/> in the same paper charging me with\n                “either ignorance<lb/> or hasty and impetuous zeal,” and cautioning the Jews\n                against<lb/> being aroused to action, since by that treaty “their rights, as\n                Americans</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3b27qh58/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
